    <div id="wrapper">
        <div id="content">
            <h2>How to use Memrise uploader</h2>
                <p>To use this add-on you just need to go to one of your courses database page and scroll till the bottom until you find a multiple input form with a button labeled "Upload".</p>
                <img src="img/multiple-button.png" alt="A image of the new form">
                <p>Choose your files and click upload, Firefox could stops for few seconds but there's nothing wrong with that.</p>
                <p>Firefox will fire a notification when files have been uploaded. Wait a few second and refresh the page to see your database populated.</p>
        </div>
        <div id"FAQ">
                <h2>F.A.Q</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Does this add-on upload all the files I'm throwing at it?</b><br>
                    <p>No, it just search for the words without audio, <span class="deleted">the next version will let you choose to upload everything instead</span> if you want to upload every file matching a word go to the addon's prefence page.</p></li>
                    <li><b>Why audio files don't appear immediately in the database page?</b><br><p>Every time a browser uploads a file to Memrise's server it receives a request to change the page appearence. I simply ignored this request because to me it was useless.</p></li>
                </ul>
        </div>
